Package geometries

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Intersectable
    Intersectable is a common interface for all geometries that are able to intersect from a ray to their entity (Shape)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cylinder
    class Cylinder extends Tube Cylinder is afinite Tube with a certain _height
    FlatGeometry  
    Geometries
    class Geometries implements Intersectable
    Geometry
    abstract class Geometry implements Intersectable interface Geometry is the basic interface for all geometric objects who are implementing getNormal method.
    Intersectable.GeoPoint
    * GeoPoint is just a tuple holding * references to a specific point ain a specific geometry
    Plane
    class Plane extends Geometry- has point and normal
    Polygon
    Polygon class represents two-dimensional polygon in 3D Cartesian coordinate system
    RadialGeometry
    RadialGeometry is an abstract class that defines all radial geometries.
    Sphere
    class Sphere extends RadialGeometry
    Triangle
    class Triangle extends Polygon- polygon with 3 vertexes.
    Tube
    Represents an infinite tube in the 3D space.
